<title>CANADA: Pangea reports gold mineralization.</title>
<headline>Pangea reports gold mineralization.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1996-09-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pangea Goldfields Inc said on Thursday it has discovered gold mineralization on its Lafontaine property in Northern Ontario.</p>
<p>Stripping has exposed a 400-metre long by 10-metre wide gold bearing folded iron formation hosting semi-massive pyrite, pyrrhotite and arsenopyrite along with numerous quartz veins, the company said in a statement.</p>
<p>Preliminary results from surface sampling confirm the presence of gold over the entire length of the formation, Pangea said.</p>
<p>Values range between 2.2 grams of gold per tonne and 3.6 grams per tonne.</p>
<p>-- Reuters Toronto Bureau 416-941-8100</p>
